description.narrative: UNICEF EAPR has strengthened capacity to design and implement gender responsive, equity focused NUTRITION programmes that deliver results for the most disadvantaged children at scale., which contributes to Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: COs practice programming excellence to achieve quality results for children at scale in both development and humanitarian settings

description.narrative: In 2021, the UNICEF EAPRO Nutrition Section maintained its new ways of assisting Country Offices through remote support. EAPRO Nutrition responded to Country Office technical support requests, facilitated learning across country contexts, advanced programming innovations, and supported emergency responses.; EAPRO Nutrition also helped to align EAP Country Programmes with the 2020-2030 Global Nutrition Strategy during key moments in Country Programme planning cycles. | Status:Met | As-of Date:10/03/2022
